The Hound of the Baskervilles is a classic mystery novel featuring the famous detective Sherlock Holmes and his loyal friend Dr. John Watson. The story revolves around the eerie legend of a spectral hound that haunts the Baskerville family. The main theme of the story is the tension between rational, scientific thinking (represented by Holmes) and superstitious beliefs (represented by the legend of the hound). The characters' thoughts and actions are driven by their beliefs and their quest to uncover the truth behind the legend.
